* supervision, access, intervention and sanctions (Chapter 11);
* the Building Committee (Chapter 12);
* appeals (Chapter 13);
* compensation for damage and compulsory purchase (Chapter 14);
* judicial review, etc. (Chapter 15); and
* authorisations (Chapter 16).

In planning, and in matters concerning building permits or advance notices in accordance with this Act, built environment and construction works must be located on land that is suited for the purpose, with regard to:
* the health and safety of people;
* land, rock, and water conditions;
* possibilities for providing traffic facilities, water supply facilities, sewerage
* possibilities to prevent water and air pollution as well as hazardous levels of
* the risk of accidents, flooding, and erosion.

Planning in accordance with this Act must take into account the requirements, within or close to area with assembled built environment, of:
* roads and streets;
* squares;
* parks and other green areas;
* suitable places for play, exercise, and other outdoor activities; and
* possibilities for a reasonable level of community and commercial service.

